'''Joyce Muskat''' was one of only four writers with no prior television credits able to sell a script to ''[[Star Trek: The Original Series]]'' ([[David Gerrold]], Judy Burns, and [[Jean Lisette Aroeste]] were the other three). ''Star Trek'' co-producer [[Robert H. Justman]] read her unsolicited script, "The Answerer",<ref>STAR TREK: THE ORIGINAL SERIES--SEASON 3 (Skybox, 1999)--Behind-The-Scenes insert #B125</ref> and recommended it be bought. It was produced as Episode 63, "[[The Empath]]" during the third and final season, and was her only sale to television.

Joyce Muskat is an active member of California's [[Society for Creative Anachronism]].<ref>Dave Eversole [http://www.fastcopyinc.com/orionpress/articles/empath.htm Story outline of "The Empath"] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080103021546/http://www.fastcopyinc.com/orionpress/articles/empath.htm |date=2008-01-03 }} Orion Press/Fast Copy website</ref><ref>Herbert Solow and Robert H. Justman, Inside Star Trek: The Real Story, Pocket Books, 1996, p.404</ref>

