{{Infobox UN resolution |number = 368 |organ = SC |date = 17 April |year = 1975 |meeting = 1,821 |code = S/RES/368 |document = https://undocs.org/S/RES/368(1975) |for = 13 |abstention = 0 |against = 0 |subject = Egypt-Israel |result = Adopted |image = Middle East (orthographic projection).svg |caption = The Middle East }}
'''[[United Nations]] [[List of UN Security Council Resolutions|Security Council Resolution]] 368''', adopted on April 17, 1975, recalled previous resolutions and considered a report from the [[United Nations Secretary-General|Secretary-General]] before calling upon the parties involved in [[Yom Kippur War#Cease-fire and immediate aftermath|the prevailing state of tension in the aftermath of the Yom Kippur War]] to immediately implement [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 338|resolution 338]]. The Council then renewed the mandate of the [[United Nations Emergency Force]] for another three months until July 24, 1975, and requested the Secretary-General submit a report on the developments in the situation and the measures taken to implement the resolution.
The resolution was adopted by 13 votes; [[People's Republic of China|China]] and [[Iraq]] did not participate in the vote.
